.TH MARROW 1
.SH NAME
marrow \- portable distributed kernel (9P server)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B marrow
[
.I --port
.I port
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Marrow is a headless 9P-compatible kernel providing authentication,
service registry, CPU server, and graphics devices.
.PP
Features:
.TP
9P2000 Server
Complete 9P2000 file server protocol.
.TP
Authentication
dp9ik (Ed448), p9any, p9sk1, factotum, secstore.
.TP
Service Registry
Dynamic service registration and discovery via /svc.
.TP
CPU Server
Plan 9 rcpu for remote execution.
.TP
Graphics
/dev/draw, /dev/screen, /dev/mouse, /dev/kbd.
.TP
System Devices
/dev/cons, /dev/fd, /proc, /env.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --port
TCP port for 9P server (default: 17011).
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Start on default port
marrow

# Start on custom port
marrow --port 17019
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/marrow/keys
Factotum keys file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/marrow
Runtime data directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR 9p (1),
.IR drawterm (1),
.IR lib9p (4),
.IR libauth (4),
.IR libregistry (4),
.IR graphics (4)
